</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id2033690">
<problem id="fs-id1897422"><para id="fs-id1857310">Which explanation best describes why plasma proteins can function as buffers?</para>
<list id="fs-id1236251" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha">
<item>Plasma proteins combine with bicarbonate to make a stronger buffer.</item>
<item>Plasma proteins are immune to damage from acids.</item>
<item>Proteins have both positive and negative charges on their surface.</item>
<item>Proteins are alkaline.</item>
</list>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1632435">
<label/>
<para id="fs-id1895221">C</para>
</solution>
